// useDataLoader
// Loads sessions and session items from the API and populates the session store.

All load operations track a shared isLoading/error state.
Session items include diagrams, documents, designs, spreadsheets, and snippets.

FUNCTION useDataLoader() -> UseDataLoaderReturn                                 EXPORT
  CALLS: api (api), useSessionStore (sessionStore)
  Manages state: isLoading, error.
  Exposes: loadSessions, loadSessionItems, refreshSessionItems,
  selectDiagramWithContent, selectDocumentWithContent, selectDesignWithContent, selectSpreadsheetWithContent.

---

FUNCTION loadSessions()
  CALLS: api (api)
  Fetches all sessions from the API and writes them to the store.

---

FUNCTION loadCollabState(project, session)
  CALLS: api (api)
  Fetches collab session state from the API and writes it to the store.
  On failure, sets collabState to null.

---

FUNCTION loadSessionItems(project, session)
  CALLS: api (api), loadCollabState
  Fetches diagrams, documents, designs, spreadsheets, and snippets in parallel.
  Writes all results to the store, then loads the collab state.

---

FUNCTION refreshSessionItems(project, session)
  CALLS: loadSessionItems
  Captures the current item selection, reloads all session items, then re-applies the previous selection
  if those items still exist in the refreshed data.

---

FUNCTION selectDiagramWithContent(project, session, id)
  CALLS: api (api)
  Immediately sets the selected diagram in the store for instant UI feedback, then fetches the full
  diagram content from the API and updates the store entry with it.

---

FUNCTION selectDocumentWithContent(project, session, id)
  CALLS: api (api)
  Same pattern as selectDiagramWithContent but for documents.

---

FUNCTION selectDesignWithContent(project, session, id)
  CALLS: api (api)
  Same pattern as selectDiagramWithContent but for designs.

---

FUNCTION selectSpreadsheetWithContent(project, session, id)
  CALLS: api (api)
  Same pattern as selectDiagramWithContent but for spreadsheets.
